# Business & Technical Decisions Log

## Physical SIM Strategy
- **Only US data plans** sold as physical SIM cards (for now)
- Uses **eUICC** technology — Red Tea eSIM profiles stored in physical SIM cards
- Factory (CSM) pre-writes and pre-enables profiles
- Activation in H5 = **binding only** (associates card with customer account)
- Login required before binding

## Billing Problem (Red Tea)
- Red Tea charges when profile is **enabled**, not when data is first used
- This means factory-enabled cards lose validity days during shipping
- **Decision**: Push Red Tea to implement "charge on first data use"
- **Status**: Waiting for Red Tea to update their system

## Future Native App
- Plan to upgrade H5 to native Android app
- Will integrate LPA via OMAPI for direct eUICC profile management
- CSM needs to pre-write app signing certificate hash into ARA-M access rules on chips
- Reference implementations: OpenEUICC / EasyEUICC

## Data Service Layer (留口子)
- All API calls go through `services/dataService.ts`
- Currently uses supplier API (Red Tea) directly
- Backend API at `evair.zhhwxt.cn` exists but only has 15 packages (needs 2,489)
- When backend is ready, flip one config flag in dataService.ts to switch

## eSIM Installation Rules
- eSIM profiles can only be **downloaded/installed ONCE** from SM-DP+ server (standard GSMA behavior)
- SM-DP+ status flow: RELEASED → DOWNLOADED → INSTALLED → ENABLED → DISABLED
- If customer deletes profile from device, it cannot be re-downloaded — they need a new purchase
- Install modal displays amber warning: "One-time installation only"
- Warning translated in EN, ZH, ES

## Features Removed
- **Bottom navigation bar**: Removed — blocked too much screen area on mobile
- **Large "Install Your eSIM" center block**: Removed from My eSIMs page — replaced with compact banner indicator + row below donut

## i18n Policy
- Every user-facing string MUST use `t()` translation keys
- Three languages: English (en), Chinese (zh), Spanish (es)
- Chinese translations are for both customers and internal staff communications

## Marketplace Sales
- SIM cards also sold on Amazon.com and Temu.com
- Marketplace customers download H5 app to activate/bind their cards
- Same binding flow works for both in-app and marketplace purchases

## Supplier API Centralization (in progress, 2026-04)
- **Decision**: All supplier API calls (Red Tea / PCCW) MUST go through Laravel backend at `evair.zhhwxt.cn`.
- **Reason**: prevents supplier credential/SKU leak to browser; lets admin team control pricing/visibility centrally.
- **H5 catalogue migrated to backend**: `/v1/h5/packages*` endpoints serve packages, hot list, locations, recharge.
- **Direct ESIMAccess calls being removed** from `services/esimApi.ts`. New code MUST use `services/dataService.ts` only.
- Order placement + Stripe payment + provisioning still flow through Netlify functions for now (separate migration).

